The issue is that the loop condition accesses the state variable `this.countArray.length` on every iteration, which can cause performance problems. To fix this, we cache the state variable in a local variable before the loop and modify the loop to remove elements from the end to avoid index shifting issues.

Here's the fix:

```diff
--- a/entry/src/main/ets/MainAbility/pages/MonitoringSample.ets
+++ b/entry/src/main/ets/MainAbility/pages/MonitoringSample.ets
@@ -191,8 +191,10 @@
   }

   clearAllCountArray() {
-    for (let i = 0; i < this.countArray.length; i++) {
-      ArrayHelper.removeIndex(this.countArray, i);
+    let arr = this.countArray;
+    let len = arr.length;
+    for (let i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
+      ArrayHelper.removeIndex(arr, i);
     }
   }

